  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (31fcf5a 2023-05-19T00:10:33.861185000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script --broadcast\n\n### Operating System\n\nNone\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen running a deployment script, the sequence seems to be running with `--slow` by default, and ain't no way of setting it to fast. I'd like all the txs to be signed and broadcast, without expecting the receipt of the previous one to execute the next one. Risky take, but it'd save a lot of time in large testnet deployments.",
